<!--Change refentry id and indexterm id-->
<refentry id="filereadmeta">
  <indexterm id="Indexfilereadmeta"><primary>filereadmeta</primary></indexterm>
  <!--Make sure the category below is a valid one! See categories.py-->
  <refentryinfo><title>Signal I/O:Soundfile Queries</title></refentryinfo>
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>filereadmeta</refentrytitle>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>filereadmeta</refname>
    <refpurpose>
      Read metadata from a soundfile
    </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <section xml:id="description">
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      Reads metadata from a soundfile via libsndfile. Only a subset of
      keys, standardized across different fileformats, is supported:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist spacing="compact">
      <listitem>
        <para>
          title
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          comment
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          artist
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          album
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          tracknumber
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          software
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <para>
      The opcode has two forms: 1) a specific key is queried, in which
      case the opcode returns the string for that key, or an empty
      string if that key is not present; 2) no key is given and all the
      metadata is returned in two string arrays, one with all the keys
      and second with their corresponding values.
    </para>
  </section>
  
  <refsect1>
    <title>Syntax</title>
	  <!--Keep this < ~70 chars to avoid overflow in the pdf version-->
    <synopsis>Svalue <command>filereadmeta</command> Ssndfile, Skey</synopsis>
    <synopsis>Skeys[], Svalues[] <command>filereadmeta</command> Ssndfile</synopsis>
	  
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Initialization</title>
    <para>
	    <emphasis>Ssndfile</emphasis> The path to a soundfile
	  </para>
    <para>
	    <emphasis>Skey</emphasis> The metadata key to query
	  </para>
    
  </refsect1>
  
